body:
@ewencp @ijuma I made all the suggested changes, except for the one about embedded HTML in the descriptions.

This pull request was based off of trunk from 6 weeks ago. Do I need to merge trunk into the branch myself and update this PR, or will Github do it for me if/when you accept the pull request?

Thanks.

@ewencp My thoughts are similar to yours with regards to app-specific permissions. It's not clear to me that we want to drop support for that for the delete case without thinking it through.

@granthenke, we already support \* to mean all topics, right? It's used in the following test for example:
https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/test/scala/integration/kafka/api/EndToEndAuthorizationTest.scala#L98. Given that, it doesn't seem any more cumbersome than the Cluster authorization for Delete and it's more flexible.

It's also true that we would need to extend support for more complex wildcards or regex to make this more useful, but that seems like a natural extension with the current approach.

@ijuma You are right, I missed that. It is enabled by [this line](https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/security/auth/SimpleAclAuthorizer.scala#L125) in the SimpleACLAuthorizer. I will add a test to the AuthorizerIntegrationTest to verify that it works. 

I also agree regex support would be a good way to add more flexible psuedo namespace support. 

@junrao Are you okay with keeping it the way it is and using the wildcard to provide all access?
